<h3>Throttle tag options</h3>

<tt>{THROTTLE [rate|add|subtract|multiply|divide]=value [final] 
  [not] [help]}</tt>

<dl>
<dt><b>help</b>
<dd>Displays this text. Overrides all other options.
<dt><b>rate</b>
<dd>Sets this request's bandwidth to <i>value</i> bytes/second
<dt><b>add</b>
<dd>adds this request <i>value</i> bytes/second
<dt><b>subtract</b>
<dd>subtracts from this request <i>value</i> bytes/second
<dt><b>multiply</b>
<dd>multiplies this request's bandwidth by <i>value</i> (a floating-point 
  number)
<dt><b>divide</b>
<dd>divides this request's bandwidth by <i>value</i>
</dl>

<p>
<b>final</b> is a modifier: if specified, it will prevent any further
processing of bandwidth assignments for this request. Otherwise, the usual
processing by throttling modules takes place, depending from your
configuration.<br>
Notice that this tag is handled <b>after</b> the Baseline Throttling module,
and <b>before</b> all the others.

<p>
<b>not</b> overrides any other arguments except <tt>help</tt>. It will
signal that the current request is not to be throttled, and implies
<tt>final</tt>.
